  "summary": "discord_token_generator drops and executes an obfuscated Windows payload on import",
  "details": "The package presents itself as a Discord token generator but its tokens.py module concatenates eight large base64 string chunks, base64-decodes them, XOR-decodes the bytes with key 66, writes the result to %TEMP%\\tokens.tmp, and launches it via subprocess.Popen with shell=True and the CREATE_NO_WINDOW flag (0x08000000) to hide the process window. The drop-and-execute path fires at module load: a top-level TokenManager() instantiation triggers _load_tokens(), which calls notin() to perform the decode-write-execute sequence. The visible CLI prints a fake banner and emits random strings as a cover story while the embedded executable runs in the background. setup.py uses impersonation metadata (author 'DiscordDev', email 'dev@discord.com') to appear official. Installing or importing this package on Windows results in execution of an attacker-supplied binary on the installer's machine.",
